  "title": "Temporalis",
  "body_html": "<b>Overview</b><br /><ul><li>Temporalis muscle is one of the four muscles of mastication (the others being masseter, medial pterygoid and lateral pterygoid).  </li><li>It is a broad fan-shaped muscle on each side of the head that fills the temporal fossa</li></ul><br /><b>Key points</b><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th>Temporalis</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Innervation</td><td>mandibular branch of trigeminal nerve (V3)</td></tr><tr><td>Action</td><td>Elevation and retraction of the mandible</td></tr><tr><td>Origin</td><td>Temporal lines on the parietal bone of the skull and the superior temporal surface of the sphenoid bone</td></tr><tr><td>Insertion</td><td>Coronoid process of the mandible</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><i>Diagram illustrating temporalis</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti099b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti099.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><i>Diagram illustrating the temporal fossa</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb465b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb465.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temporal</td><td>fossa'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb465b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><i>Diagram illustrating temporal lines</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb466b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb466.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temporal line'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb466b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">2</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Head & neck anatomy</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\n<b>Overview</b><br /><ul><li>Temporalis muscle is one of the four muscles of mastication (the others being masseter, medial pterygoid and lateral pterygoid).  </li><li>It is a broad fan-shaped muscle on each side of the head that fills the temporal fossa</li></ul><br /><b>Key points</b><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th>Temporalis</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Innervation</td><td>mandibular branch of trigeminal nerve (V3)</td></tr><tr><td>Action</td><td>Elevation and retraction of the mandible</td></tr><tr><td>Origin</td><td>Temporal lines on the parietal bone of the skull and the superior temporal surface of the sphenoid bone</td></tr><tr><td>Insertion</td><td>Coronoid process of the mandible</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><i>Diagram illustrating temporalis</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti099b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti099.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><i>Diagram illustrating the temporal fossa</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb465b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb465.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temporal</td><td>fossa'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb465b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></CENTER><br /><i>Diagram illustrating temporal lines</i><br /><br /><CENTER><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb466b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb466.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temporal line'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:L